  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hysterectomy is one of the most performed surgery in women. Public authorities wish that
      one-day surgery become a majority and hysterectomy could be part of it in the future. The aim
      of this study is to determine the feasibility of ambulatory hysterectomy.

      Patients and methods: Investigators will realize an observational descriptive survey based on
      questionnaires in two surgical gynecology units. Women under 70 years old, who undergo
      hysterectomy will be included.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
